    "name": "M A R",
    "profile": "'10AM. Mono' by the trio M A R is an atypical album. While the voice of the French-Canadian artist Ira Lee anchors it in the hip-hop genre, the dense and rich orchestrations of Grégoire Orio (As Human Pattern, La Nòvia) & Julien Magot (Appalache) give it a peculiar identity. 10 tracks conceived as almost as many climaxes, where one crosses as many borders. A richness of tones multiplied by the presence of distinguished guests such as Jean-Michel Pirès (Bruit Noir, Numbers Not Names) who's playing on most of the material, but also Stéphane Pigneul (Oiseaux-Tempête, Le Reveil des Tropiques), and Jacques Puech from La Nòvia on 'Razzle Dazzle'. An intense instrumental road-trip that mirrors the message : words loaded with a sharp cynicism and heavy lucidity. Even if some of the tracks take on a more quirky tone ('Smoke In A Benz', 'Ouch'), the Montrealer uses the space he's given as a platform for strong social themes such as education or the animal cause ('4.30AM', 'OK! Cannibals'), or qu",
